# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CCBOT Discord Voice Bridge — configuration  (copy to `.env`)
#
# Keep this small. The bridge mirrors the APP for everything behavioural — your
# wake word, whether wake is enabled, end-of-speech silence — by reading the
# app's own settings live. Control creds arrive at runtime via /link. So .env
# only needs your Discord bot identity and how you want to hear audio.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# REQUIRED — your bot identity (see DISCORD_SETUP_GUIDE.md, Part A)
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
DISCORD_GUILD_ID=

# REQUIRED for security — Discord user IDs allowed to drive the manager (slash
# commands + auto-forwarded text). Comma-separated. The manager (terminal 999)
# is a privileged local agent, so guild membership is NOT enough. If this is
# left blank the bridge DENIES all commands and, on your first command, replies
# with your own ID so you can paste it here. (For voice, also set
# ALLOWED_SPEAKER_IDS below to the same IDs.)
DISCORD_ALLOWED_USER_IDS=

# How you hear the manager:
#   system = everything the speakers play (TTS + sound effects + wake-up alarm)  [default]
#   tts    = manager's TTS voice only (lighter; misses SFX/alarm)
AUDIO_SOURCE=system

# ── Optional ──
# Fixed fallback voice channel. Normally leave blank — the bot joins whatever
# channel you're in when you run /link (music-bot style).
# DISCORD_VOICE_CHANNEL_ID=
# Restrict whose speech is processed (comma-separated Discord user IDs).
# ALLOWED_SPEAKER_IDS=

# ── You almost certainly don't need anything below ──
# Wake word/enable come from the APP automatically. Uncomment ONLY to override
# the app for testing:
# WAKE_PHRASE=
# WAKE_WORD_ENABLED=
# Backend + audio internals (sensible defaults; override only for edge cases):
# BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8123
# PULSE_SERVER=
# SYSTEM_AUDIO_DEVICE=
# Advanced link-vault path (must match the manager's make-link-key tool):
# CCBOT_LINK_VAULT=
